        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Each bubble in the wrap is filled with air, creating pockets of insulation. These air pockets reduce heat transfer through greenhouse walls and roofs, maintaining stable internal temperatures. This is especially valuable during Malaysia's cooler months (November–February) or early mornings when seedlings benefit from consistent warmth.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Solar Heat Reflection & Moderation</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Bubble wrap reflects excess solar radiation in daytime hours while retaining warmth at night. This creates a balanced microclimate for plants. In Malaysia's intense tropical sun, this dual action prevents overheating while maintaining germination warmth for seedlings.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Cost-Effective Compared to Professional Insulation</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Polyurethane foam and glass fiber insulation are expensive. Bubble wrap costs 70–80% less while providing adequate thermal protection for small to medium greenhouses across Selangor and Malaysia.</p>

